Our brain itself
is an intricately

00:23:44.530 --> 00:23:50.920 align:middle line:84%
arranged system of neurons and
glial cells and biochemicals.

00:23:50.920 --> 00:23:52.990 align:middle line:84%
The majority of the
neurons within the brain

00:23:52.990 --> 00:23:55.610 align:middle line:84%
are actually formed
before birth.

00:23:55.610 --> 00:23:58.270 align:middle line:84%
And as the brain
develops in utero,

00:23:58.270 --> 00:24:02.620 align:middle line:84%
it forms three primary systems,
each building one on top

00:24:02.620 --> 00:24:04.030 align:middle line:90%
of the other.

00:24:04.030 --> 00:24:06.730 align:middle line:84%
Evolution has
optimized this process

00:24:06.730 --> 00:24:09.330 align:middle line:84%
for higher levels
of functioning.

00:24:09.330 --> 00:24:12.520 align:middle line:84%
And these systems build
from the bottom up

00:24:12.520 --> 00:24:15.430 align:middle line:84%
and then move from
the back to the front.

00:24:15.430 --> 00:24:19.900 align:middle line:84%
The first three systems are the
old brain, the limbic system,

00:24:19.900 --> 00:24:22.300 align:middle line:90%
and the neocortex.

00:24:22.300 --> 00:24:24.250 align:middle line:90%
What are these three systems?

00:24:24.250 --> 00:24:26.380 align:middle line:84%
Well, let's start
with the old brain.

00:24:26.380 --> 00:24:31.070 align:middle line:84%
The old brain starts developing
three weeks after conception,

00:24:31.070 --> 00:24:34.150 align:middle line:84%
and it primarily develops
during the second trimester

00:24:34.150 --> 00:24:37.720 align:middle line:84%
of pregnancy, continuing,
though, through age 1

00:24:37.720 --> 00:24:39.220 align:middle line:90%
after birth.

00:24:39.220 --> 00:24:41.440 align:middle line:10%
The structures
within the old brain

00:24:41.440 --> 00:24:44.860 align:middle line:10%
include the hindbrain, which
is composed of the brain

00:24:44.860 --> 00:24:49.420 align:middle line:10%
stem, the pons, the medulla
oblongata, and the cerebellum,

00:24:49.420 --> 00:24:51.730 align:middle line:10%
as well as the
midbrain, which is

00:24:51.730 --> 00:24:55.570 align:middle line:10%
related to our sense
of touch and balance.

00:24:55.570 --> 00:24:58.780 align:middle line:10%
The next system building off of
the foundation of the old brain

00:24:58.780 --> 00:25:02.200 align:middle line:10%
is the limbic system,
which primarily develops

00:25:02.200 --> 00:25:05.770 align:middle line:10%
as toddlers up to the age of 5.

00:25:05.770 --> 00:25:08.860 align:middle line:10%
This is the functioning
of our reward centers--

00:25:08.860 --> 00:25:11.640 align:middle line:10%
the fight or flight
response as well.

00:25:11.640 --> 00:25:13.420 align:middle line:10%
The structures within
the limbic system

00:25:13.420 --> 00:25:17.030 align:middle line:10%
include the thalamus, the
hypothalamus, the hippocampus,

00:25:17.030 --> 00:25:19.660 align:middle line:10%
the amygdala, and
the basal ganglia.

00:25:19.660 --> 00:25:23.560 align:middle line:10%
The limbic system relates mostly
to our emotions, our long term

00:25:23.560 --> 00:25:26.620 align:middle line:10%
memory, spatial
mapping, and it's also

00:25:26.620 --> 00:25:30.370 align:middle line:10%
related to our sense
of hearing and smell.

00:25:30.370 --> 00:25:34.450 align:middle line:84%
As we move higher, then,
into the neocortex, this area

00:25:34.450 --> 00:25:37.570 align:middle line:84%
is primarily developed
during childhood,

00:25:37.570 --> 00:25:40.090 align:middle line:84%
with the right hemisphere
dominating development

00:25:40.090 --> 00:25:44.620 align:middle line:84%
between the ages of 4 to 7
years old, and then synthesizing

00:25:44.620 --> 00:25:48.460 align:middle line:84%
the right and left hemispheres
from the age of 7 to 11 years

00:25:48.460 --> 00:25:49.440 align:middle line:90%
old.

00:25:49.440 --> 00:25:55.420 align:middle line:84%
The neocortex is fully developed
by around the age 15 years old.

00:25:55.420 --> 00:25:58.510 align:middle line:84%
The primary structures
within the neocortex

00:25:58.510 --> 00:26:02.230 align:middle line:84%
are the left and right
hemispheres of the cerebrum.

00:26:02.230 --> 00:26:05.710 align:middle line:84%
These include the frontal,
temporal, parietal,

00:26:05.710 --> 00:26:07.760 align:middle line:90%
and occipital lobes.

00:26:07.760 --> 00:26:10.210 align:middle line:84%
This area of the brain
is related to our sense

00:26:10.210 --> 00:26:12.330 align:middle line:90%
of vision and hearing.

00:26:12.330 --> 00:26:16.180 align:middle line:84%
It relates to our imagination
memory, attention,

00:26:16.180 --> 00:26:21.160 align:middle line:84%
language capacities, perceptual
awareness, spatial reasoning,

00:26:21.160 --> 00:26:23.830 align:middle line:90%
and motor commands.

00:26:23.830 --> 00:26:26.470 align:middle line:90%
After birth, the fourth system--

00:26:26.470 --> 00:26:30.070 align:middle line:84%
the prefrontal cortex
at the very forehead--

00:26:30.070 --> 00:26:32.620 align:middle line:90%
begins to rapidly develop.

00:26:32.620 --> 00:26:36.400 align:middle line:84%
This is the part of the brain
that makes us the most human.

00:26:36.400 --> 00:26:38.860 align:middle line:84%
It is our executive
control center,

00:26:38.860 --> 00:26:40.840 align:middle line:84%
and it is responsible
for decision

00:26:40.840 --> 00:26:44.620 align:middle line:84%
making, planning-- it
helps form our personality

00:26:44.620 --> 00:26:46.450 align:middle line:90%
and our expression.

00:26:46.450 --> 00:26:49.300 align:middle line:84%
This prefrontal cortex
is what orchestrates

00:26:49.300 --> 00:26:52.940 align:middle line:84%
the leadership over the other
three systems of the brain--

00:26:52.940 --> 00:26:55.240 align:middle line:84%
at least, that's
what's intended.

00:26:55.240 --> 00:26:57.820 align:middle line:84%
This foremost part of
the brain is actually

00:26:57.820 --> 00:27:00.790 align:middle line:84%
the last to develop
after birth, and it

00:27:00.790 --> 00:27:05.930 align:middle line:84%
continues developing all
the way up to about age 25.

00:27:05.930 --> 00:27:08.000 align:middle line:84%
Beyond these four
brain systems, science

00:27:08.000 --> 00:27:10.250 align:middle line:84%
is now also beginning
to realize that we

00:27:10.250 --> 00:27:12.980 align:middle line:84%
have two other very
important systems that

00:27:12.980 --> 00:27:17.010 align:middle line:84%
are part of the nervous
system and the brain.

00:27:17.010 --> 00:27:20.780 align:middle line:84%
And these two parts include
the heart and the gut.

00:27:20.780 --> 00:27:22.640 align:middle line:84%
The heart influences
the functions

00:27:22.640 --> 00:27:25.220 align:middle line:84%
of the brain in
significant ways,

00:27:25.220 --> 00:27:28.350 align:middle line:84%
maintaining a two-way
communication between the heart

00:27:28.350 --> 00:27:29.150 align:middle line:90%
and the brain.

00:27:29.150 --> 00:27:32.690 align:middle line:84%
And the heart is constantly
sending signals to the brain.

00:27:32.690 --> 00:27:34.940 align:middle line:84%
It communicates through
the nerve cells,

00:27:34.940 --> 00:27:37.250 align:middle line:84%
through hormones,
through pressure waves,

00:27:37.250 --> 00:27:40.900 align:middle line:84%
and through the heart's
massive electromagnetic field.

00:27:40.900 --> 00:27:43.340 align:middle line:84%
As the rhythms of the
heart become more coherent,

00:27:43.340 --> 00:27:46.670 align:middle line:84%
we experience shifts in
our perception, increased

00:27:46.670 --> 00:27:50.780 align:middle line:84%
mental clarity, and heightened
intuitive awareness.

00:27:50.780 --> 00:27:54.240 align:middle line:10%
The deepest part of
this system is the gut,

00:27:54.240 --> 00:27:59.030 align:middle line:10%
and it also contains over
100 million nerve cells,

00:27:59.030 --> 00:28:04.700 align:middle line:10%
forming what scientists now
call an enteric nervous system.

00:28:04.700 --> 00:28:08.060 align:middle line:84%
An imbalance in the gut has
been connected to things

00:28:08.060 --> 00:28:10.580 align:middle line:84%
like anxiety and
depression, affecting

00:28:10.580 --> 00:28:15.500 align:middle line:84%
our mood, our cognition,
and our behaviors.

00:28:15.500 --> 00:28:18.800 align:middle line:84%
Studies show that relaxation
techniques such as meditation

00:28:18.800 --> 00:28:23.720 align:middle line:84%
and yoga help to relieve
gut-related imbalances.

00:28:23.720 --> 00:28:26.060 align:middle line:84%
It is clear that our
brain-body system

00:28:26.060 --> 00:28:29.090 align:middle line:84%
is more than just
the sum of its parts.

00:28:29.090 --> 00:28:34.130 align:middle line:84%
It is operating as a complex
and interconnected system.

00:28:34.130 --> 00:28:37.460 align:middle line:84%
As we see from this journey
through the fetal development,

00:28:37.460 --> 00:28:40.470 align:middle line:84%
not only does the brain
develop from the bottom up,

00:28:40.470 --> 00:28:43.010 align:middle line:84%
but MRI studies have also
shown that it then moves

00:28:43.010 --> 00:28:44.855 align:middle line:90%
from the back to the front.

00:28:44.855 --> 00:28:48.420 align:middle line:84%
But why is this important
for us to understand?

00:28:48.420 --> 00:28:50.790 align:middle line:84%
Well, we have to know
how the brain was

00:28:50.790 --> 00:28:55.110 align:middle line:84%
built in order to work our
way back to the foundations.

00:28:55.110 --> 00:28:57.750 align:middle line:84%
We tend to have more
conscious awareness

00:28:57.750 --> 00:29:01.020 align:middle line:84%
of the prefrontal cortex
and the neocortex,

00:29:01.020 --> 00:29:03.180 align:middle line:84%
while the deeper brain
and the limbic system

00:29:03.180 --> 00:29:05.370 align:middle line:84%
are usually operating
subconsciously or

00:29:05.370 --> 00:29:07.380 align:middle line:90%
unconsciously.

00:29:07.380 --> 00:29:11.220 align:middle line:84%
As we embark on
rewiring our brain,

00:29:11.220 --> 00:29:14.670 align:middle line:84%
we begin working our
way from the front

00:29:14.670 --> 00:29:17.670 align:middle line:84%
backwards and then
down, starting

00:29:17.670 --> 00:29:19.650 align:middle line:84%
where we can create
this intention

00:29:19.650 --> 00:29:22.650 align:middle line:84%
from a conscious level, and
then working our way back

00:29:22.650 --> 00:29:25.620 align:middle line:84%
to the deeper
foundations of the brain.

00:29:25.620 --> 00:29:28.620 align:middle line:84%
And while we may be able to
compare parts of the brain

00:29:28.620 --> 00:29:30.970 align:middle line:84%
to different
developmental stages,

00:29:30.970 --> 00:29:33.300 align:middle line:90%
this is a very simplified model.

00:29:33.300 --> 00:29:36.850 align:middle line:84%
The brain itself is not
composed of separate parts,

00:29:36.850 --> 00:29:40.230 align:middle line:84%
but it functions in
a very connected way.

00:29:40.230 --> 00:29:45.210 align:middle line:84%
The average neuron has anywhere
between 1,000 to 10,000

00:29:45.210 --> 00:29:47.130 align:middle line:90%
synaptic connections.

00:29:47.130 --> 00:29:50.160 align:middle line:84%
And beyond this, there are
biochemical communications

00:29:50.160 --> 00:29:52.170 align:middle line:84%
between the brain and
the rest of the body

00:29:52.170 --> 00:29:54.750 align:middle line:84%
through neuropeptides
and hormones

00:29:54.750 --> 00:29:56.910 align:middle line:90%
and the endocrine glands.

00:29:56.910 --> 00:30:00.330 align:middle line:84%
This inter-system
connectivity provides us

00:30:00.330 --> 00:30:04.920 align:middle line:84%
the framework to enhance the
connectivity of the brain.

00:30:04.920 --> 00:30:07.440 align:middle line:84%
To bring our waking
consciousness

00:30:07.440 --> 00:30:10.900 align:middle line:84%
into a more transcendent
state of awareness,

00:30:10.900 --> 00:30:15.210 align:middle line:84%
we must become more conscious
of the whole brain function.

00:30:15.210 --> 00:30:18.600 align:middle line:84%
In an ideal situation,
if everything goes well

00:30:18.600 --> 00:30:21.120 align:middle line:84%
during the brain's development,
and if everything is

00:30:21.120 --> 00:30:23.080 align:middle line:90%
operating in perfect harmony--

00:30:23.080 --> 00:30:25.050 align:middle line:84%
we have built those
proper connections

00:30:25.050 --> 00:30:26.370 align:middle line:90%
through our growth--

00:30:26.370 --> 00:30:29.040 align:middle line:84%
we should be almost
like super humans

00:30:29.040 --> 00:30:31.750 align:middle line:90%
by the time we're in our 20s.

00:30:31.750 --> 00:30:33.070 align:middle line:90%
So what went wrong?

00:30:33.070 --> 00:30:36.120 align:middle line:84%
Well, typically, there are
breakdowns that happen.

00:30:36.120 --> 00:30:38.340 align:middle line:84%
We experience
improper programming

00:30:38.340 --> 00:30:40.800 align:middle line:90%
during the developmental stages.

00:30:40.800 --> 00:30:44.300 align:middle line:84%
There's emotional and mental
attachments that can come in.

00:30:44.300 --> 00:30:47.010 align:middle line:84%
And while the evolutionary
pattern guided our brain

00:30:47.010 --> 00:30:49.710 align:middle line:84%
development from the
bottom up, it often

00:30:49.710 --> 00:30:53.610 align:middle line:84%
did so in a chaotic
and stochastic way.

00:30:53.610 --> 00:30:56.850 align:middle line:84%
We experienced trauma,
and faulty inputs,

00:30:56.850 --> 00:30:59.470 align:middle line:84%
leading to bad habits,
and as a result,

00:30:59.470 --> 00:31:02.430 align:middle line:84%
the bridges between
the different systems

00:31:02.430 --> 00:31:04.170 align:middle line:90%
are incomplete.

00:31:04.170 --> 00:31:06.660 align:middle line:84%
There's connections that
are missing and damaged

00:31:06.660 --> 00:31:08.920 align:middle line:90%
through this process.

00:31:08.920 --> 00:31:11.370 align:middle line:84%
Now, if all really does
go well, the brain systems

00:31:11.370 --> 00:31:14.640 align:middle line:84%
build in succession through
the developmental stages

00:31:14.640 --> 00:31:16.740 align:middle line:84%
with the proper
connections forming

00:31:16.740 --> 00:31:18.810 align:middle line:90%
at each phase of development.

00:31:18.810 --> 00:31:20.940 align:middle line:84%
Fully integrating
these brain systems

00:31:20.940 --> 00:31:24.660 align:middle line:84%
gives us huge potential
to learn, adapt,

00:31:24.660 --> 00:31:27.270 align:middle line:90%
and go beyond limitations.

00:31:27.270 --> 00:31:31.650 align:middle line:84%
But when those communications
and proper linking break down,

00:31:31.650 --> 00:31:35.460 align:middle line:90%
we become our own worst enemy.

00:31:35.460 --> 00:31:38.070 align:middle line:84%
We fall into
self-sabotage patterns.

00:31:38.070 --> 00:31:40.680 align:middle line:84%
We get caught up in
limited thinking,

00:31:40.680 --> 00:31:44.580 align:middle line:84%
and we have loads of
emotional baggage.

00:31:44.580 --> 00:31:48.990 align:middle line:84%
And our task is now to
consciously repair the system

00:31:48.990 --> 00:31:52.710 align:middle line:84%
so that we can access all
of our potential and optimal

00:31:52.710 --> 00:31:54.480 align:middle line:90%
functioning.

00:31:54.480 --> 00:31:57.270 align:middle line:84%
The Tree of Life
provides the map

00:31:57.270 --> 00:32:01.470 align:middle line:84%
showing us the pattern and how
to bring this intricate system

00:32:01.470 --> 00:32:02.970 align:middle line:90%
into balance.

00:32:02.970 --> 00:32:06.150 align:middle line:84%
We can relate these levels of
development to the pathways

00:32:06.150 --> 00:32:09.600 align:middle line:84%
on the Tree of Life and
retrace our way back

00:32:09.600 --> 00:32:12.120 align:middle line:84%
through the
evolutionary process,

00:32:12.120 --> 00:32:15.360 align:middle line:84%
building a more conscious
and connected system

00:32:15.360 --> 00:32:18.390 align:middle line:84%
that allows for optimal
functioning and expanded

00:32:18.390 --> 00:32:20.980 align:middle line:90%
states of consciousness.

00:32:20.980 --> 00:32:23.400 align:middle line:84%
So are we doomed to
our previous wiring

00:32:23.400 --> 00:32:25.440 align:middle line:90%
and all the faulty programming?

00:32:25.440 --> 00:32:27.420 align:middle line:90%
Fortunately, no.

00:32:27.420 --> 00:32:29.940 align:middle line:84%
Because of the
neuroplasticity of the brain,

00:32:29.940 --> 00:32:32.850 align:middle line:84%
we have the ability to
rewire and strengthen

00:32:32.850 --> 00:32:36.150 align:middle line:84%
these faulty connections,
and we can do this

00:32:36.150 --> 00:32:40.350 align:middle line:84%
through our spiritual practice,
through our lifestyle choices,

00:32:40.350 --> 00:32:42.270 align:middle line:84%
and through a
willingness to let go

00:32:42.270 --> 00:32:44.830 align:middle line:90%
of our emotional attachments.

00:32:44.830 --> 00:32:47.220 align:middle line:84%
This rewiring
process is only going

00:32:47.220 --> 00:32:49.980 align:middle line:84%
to happen through us
making the right choices

00:32:49.980 --> 00:32:52.440 align:middle line:90%
and taking the right actions.

00:32:52.440 --> 00:32:55.260 align:middle line:84%
And for this, our attitude
and our ways of thinking

00:32:55.260 --> 00:32:59.460 align:middle line:84%
are 95% of the battle of what
determines our ability to truly

00:32:59.460 --> 00:33:02.410 align:middle line:90%
rewire the brain-body system.

00:33:02.410 --> 00:33:04.920 align:middle line:90%
So how do we start this process?

00:33:04.920 --> 00:33:09.600 align:middle line:84%
Well, the first step to
start reprogramming the brain

00:33:09.600 --> 00:33:13.470 align:middle line:84%
is to bring our sympathetic and
parasympathetic nervous systems

00:33:13.470 --> 00:33:15.030 align:middle line:90%
into balance.

00:33:15.030 --> 00:33:17.730 align:middle line:84%
If we're in overdrive
all the time,

00:33:17.730 --> 00:33:22.030 align:middle line:84%
we're not going to allow
any rewiring to happen.

00:33:22.030 --> 00:33:26.040 align:middle line:84%
We need to start first
by relaxing the body,

00:33:26.040 --> 00:33:29.880 align:middle line:84%
focusing on the breath,
relaxing the muscles,

00:33:29.880 --> 00:33:33.740 align:middle line:84%
emptying your mind
of any thoughts.

00:33:33.740 --> 00:33:37.880 align:middle line:84%
One exercise to work with is
to practice tuning your radio

00:33:37.880 --> 00:33:42.350 align:middle line:84%
dial into connecting to the
universal consciousness.

00:33:42.350 --> 00:33:47.270 align:middle line:84%
We do this by tuning to the zero
point field, or the quiet pond.

00:33:47.270 --> 00:33:50.270 align:middle line:84%
This can be done with
a simple visualization

00:33:50.270 --> 00:33:54.050 align:middle line:84%
to bring your mind
into the state.

00:33:54.050 --> 00:33:58.970 align:middle line:84%
So to begin, close your eyes
and take a few deep breaths,

00:33:58.970 --> 00:34:04.220 align:middle line:84%
imagining the ocean, the
universal sea of consciousness.

00:34:04.220 --> 00:34:05.900 align:middle line:90%
See the waves.

00:34:05.900 --> 00:34:09.080 align:middle line:84%
Visualize and sense and
begin to imagine yourself

00:34:09.080 --> 00:34:16.560 align:middle line:84%
as a part of these waves,
and then sink deeper

00:34:16.560 --> 00:34:18.389 align:middle line:90%
into the ocean.

00:34:18.389 --> 00:34:24.489 align:middle line:84%
Sink below the waves, becoming
a part of the ocean depth.

00:34:24.489 --> 00:34:27.190 align:middle line:84%
The deeper you sink
into the ocean,

00:34:27.190 --> 00:34:31.489 align:middle line:84%
also bring the ocean
into stillness.

00:34:31.489 --> 00:34:33.980 align:middle line:84%
Begin to connect
to the background

00:34:33.980 --> 00:34:36.035 align:middle line:90%
of stillness within the ocean.

00:34:36.035 --> 00:34:39.500 align:middle line:90%


00:34:39.500 --> 00:34:42.500 align:middle line:84%
As we connect into
that stillness,

00:34:42.500 --> 00:34:47.690 align:middle line:84%
it helps us to relax, to
surrender, and to normalize

00:34:47.690 --> 00:34:48.530 align:middle line:90%
to ground state.

00:34:48.530 --> 00:34:54.800 align:middle line:90%


00:34:54.800 --> 00:34:59.000 align:middle line:84%
Practicing meditation every
day by bringing the mind

00:34:59.000 --> 00:35:02.120 align:middle line:84%
into that state of
stillness is a powerful tool

00:35:02.120 --> 00:35:05.360 align:middle line:84%
to start building
this first bridge.

00:35:05.360 --> 00:35:08.090 align:middle line:84%
We'll continue building
off of this foundation

00:35:08.090 --> 00:35:11.960 align:middle line:84%
in other episodes, working
our way through each system

00:35:11.960 --> 00:35:14.150 align:middle line:90%
of the brain and body.

00:35:14.150 --> 00:35:17.420 align:middle line:84%
Each new bridge we build
is retracing the steps

00:35:17.420 --> 00:35:21.050 align:middle line:84%
of our brain's development
to repair and enhance

00:35:21.050 --> 00:35:23.510 align:middle line:84%
the connections of
our brain regions.

00:35:23.510 --> 00:35:26.990 align:middle line:84%
For more optimal
functioning, join me again

00:35:26.990 --> 00:35:31.520 align:middle line:84%
